1
00:00:21,208 --> 00:00:23,000
[KIRARA]
He chooses for us, in silence,

2
00:00:23,083 --> 00:00:24,666
and expects us to follow?

3
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:28,166
Any hope I had of understand
this man is quickly fading...

4
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:29,375
Lower your voice!

5
00:00:29,458 --> 00:00:31,208
Or do you want us to
be caught and gutted?

6
00:00:31,291 --> 00:00:32,458
No...

7
00:00:32,541 --> 00:00:34,583
Now you are making
me beautiful, aren't you?

8
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:35,916
Oh, naturally...

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Though you won't be as
lovely as Eminosuke here.

10
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:43,125
We're doomed...!
The two of you have gone insane!

11
00:00:48,083 --> 00:00:49,541
Would you please stop with that?

12
00:00:49,625 --> 00:00:51,291
Oh, you can try to hide it...

13
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:55,625
But... I can tell that you are
totally in love with her!

14
00:00:55,708 --> 00:00:57,541
[KIKUCHIYO LAUGHS]

15
00:00:57,625 --> 00:00:59,750
[KIKUCHIYO] Oh, I think
you might be right, sprout!

16
00:00:59,833 --> 00:01:01,083
Look at him blush!

17
00:01:01,166 --> 00:01:03,958
[KIRARA] Thank you saving
my life, Great Samurai.

18
00:01:04,041 --> 00:01:06,125
Thanks for the stitch.

19
00:01:10,083 --> 00:01:12,750
I'd say our journey
went... well.

20
00:01:15,166 --> 00:01:17,458
Yeah, I guess so.

21
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:25,791
♪ opening song ♪

22
00:03:10,416 --> 00:03:13,250
[GOROBE]
Slacking off. What a surprise.

23
00:03:15,291 --> 00:03:15,958
Have they left?

24
00:03:16,041 --> 00:03:17,458
Yeah, just now...

25
00:03:17,541 --> 00:03:22,041
So, uh... do we really have
to get in that nasty thing?

26
00:03:27,333 --> 00:03:29,541
[FLIES BUZZ]

27
00:03:29,625 --> 00:03:31,000
Where's Kiku?

28
00:03:31,083 --> 00:03:32,833
We don't know
where he is right now.

29
00:03:32,916 --> 00:03:36,000
I just hope he doesn't
cause any more trouble.

30
00:03:41,333 --> 00:03:42,416
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

31
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,750
[KIKUCHIYO]
The way of the samurai

32
00:03:43,833 --> 00:03:46,458
is to always climb... up.

33
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:57,250
It's... quiet...

34
00:03:59,375 --> 00:04:00,500
[KOMACHI]
Hey! Come out!

35
00:04:00,583 --> 00:04:02,666
The samurai are here!

36
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,541
[RIKICHI]
Where are they?!

37
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,833
Hey, quit being rude!
The samurai are here!

38
00:04:11,916 --> 00:04:13,083
Come on! Say hello!

39
00:04:13,166 --> 00:04:14,333
What are you doing...?

40
00:04:14,416 --> 00:04:17,708
The samurai are here!
This is dishonorable!

41
00:04:18,791 --> 00:04:21,250
So this is
our fortress, huh?

42
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:23,416
The samurai are here...

43
00:04:23,500 --> 00:04:27,291
So where the hell
is everybody?!

44
00:04:27,375 --> 00:04:29,583
I'll inform the
Elder you're here.

45
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:43,666
[KOMACHI BREATHES HEAVILY]

46
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:44,875
[OKARA]
Welcome back.

47
00:04:44,958 --> 00:04:47,250
[KOMACHI] Huh?

48
00:04:47,333 --> 00:04:50,333
Okara! Hey, where
is everybody else?

49
00:04:50,416 --> 00:04:51,666
[OKARA]
Hiding of course...

50
00:04:51,750 --> 00:04:53,208
They're all afraid
of the samurai.

51
00:04:53,291 --> 00:04:55,291
Hiding?
But sister and Rikichi

52
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:57,916
went to a lot of trouble
to bring them all here.

53
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:01,250
Manzo made a big
fuss, as usual.

54
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:03,041
You know what
a coward he is.

55
00:05:03,125 --> 00:05:05,041
C'mon, hurry!

56
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,541
We're waiting for your sister.

57
00:05:06,625 --> 00:05:08,291
Dad! What are you doing?!

58
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,041
The samurai will
be here any day!

59
00:05:10,125 --> 00:05:12,208
You're going into hiding
with the rest of the girls!

60
00:05:12,291 --> 00:05:14,208
No! I want to
see the samurai.

61
00:05:14,291 --> 00:05:15,666
Do not be foolish, child!

62
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:18,000
How can you do this when
they're coming to save us?!

63
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:20,041
The samurai aren't
coming to save us!

64
00:05:20,125 --> 00:05:22,083
They're coming to take
our food and our women

65
00:05:22,166 --> 00:05:24,083
like they always have!

66
00:05:24,166 --> 00:05:25,875
[OKARA] So now all the women

67
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:28,208
are in the hidden
storehouse with the food.

68
00:05:28,291 --> 00:05:31,333
So, how come you're not hiding
out with the rest of them?

69
00:05:31,416 --> 00:05:32,416
[OKARA]
I don't know.

70
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:34,083
Well, I guess
this just means

71
00:05:34,166 --> 00:05:37,000
you'll get to meet
the samurai first!

72
00:05:37,083 --> 00:05:40,291
[KIKUCHIYO]
A hidden storehouse...

73
00:05:40,375 --> 00:05:43,750
Where is it, girl? Hmm?

74
00:05:45,041 --> 00:05:46,083
What's that thing?

75
00:05:46,166 --> 00:05:47,500
Oh, that's Kiku!

76
00:05:47,583 --> 00:05:48,750
[KIKUCHIYO]
Call me Kikuchiyo!

77
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:50,416
So what is he? Your sidekick?

78
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:51,833
[KIKUCHIYO] Huh?!

79
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:57,541
[FOOTSTEPS]

80
00:05:57,625 --> 00:06:00,916
I've found them--
they're at the Elder's now.

81
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,125
I'm so sorry.

82
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:04,500
Please forgive this
unfriendly welcome.

83
00:06:16,458 --> 00:06:19,916
Kiku, is this another test
of braveness or something?

84
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,416
[KIKUCHIYO] Hah, hah...

85
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:25,250
This time it's a test to see
if all farmers think alike.

86
00:06:28,125 --> 00:06:32,541
They are not going to fool me.

87
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:37,291
Ha, ha, ha! Found it.

88
00:06:37,375 --> 00:06:39,250
This is the
storehouse, isn't it?

89
00:06:39,333 --> 00:06:42,166
Come on, Kiku...

90
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:44,791
[KIKUCHIYO] 
Sorry about this, sprout, but...

91
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:50,333
Uh-oh...!

92
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:52,125
[KIKUCHIYO YELLS]

93
00:06:52,208 --> 00:06:54,958
[OKARA LAUGHS]

94
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:01,208
[ELDER]
Farmers are foolish people.

95
00:07:01,291 --> 00:07:03,583
Always worrying
about something.

96
00:07:03,666 --> 00:07:07,916
Too much rain, too much sun,
strong winds, no winds.

97
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:11,166
They wake up worrying and
they go to bed the same way.

98
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:12,666
Today's no exception.

99
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:15,583
They're just scared--
pointlessly scared.

100
00:07:15,666 --> 00:07:17,250
[MANZO] Please go away!

101
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:19,916
Doesn't anyone remember what
the bandits said they'd do to us

102
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,458
if they find out samurai
have actually arrived?

103
00:07:22,541 --> 00:07:24,666
I'm not sure what you think
we came here for, good farmer,

104
00:07:24,750 --> 00:07:26,875
but it certainly wasn't to
watch you all be slaughtered

105
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,458
by the Bandits
while we do nothing.

106
00:07:28,541 --> 00:07:30,000
But they're Bandits!

107
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,708
Yeah, think we covered that--
what's your point?

108
00:07:32,791 --> 00:07:35,291
He mentioned threats--
have they come recently?

109
00:07:35,375 --> 00:07:36,791
[ELDER] Two days ago.

110
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:38,791
They heard we had
hired samurai,

111
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:41,291
said they would kill
us if it were true.

112
00:07:41,375 --> 00:07:44,333
Then Great Elder... what
exactly do the villagers

113
00:07:44,416 --> 00:07:47,375
expect us to do
now that we're here?

114
00:07:48,875 --> 00:07:51,041
[KIKUCHIYO]
Well... look what I found!

115
00:07:51,125 --> 00:07:56,291
Rice and women!
Whaddya know? Huh?

116
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:58,000
Thought you could hide
the goods from me,

117
00:07:58,083 --> 00:08:00,375
but I'm too smart for farmers!

118
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:01,125
Shino!

119
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:03,333
Give back our rice!

120
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:06,583
[KIKUCHIYO]
Back off, suckers! Ahhh!

121
00:08:06,666 --> 00:08:07,875
Shino!

122
00:08:07,958 --> 00:08:09,416
How'd you find the hidden
storehouse, samurai?

123
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:11,375
[KIKUCHIYO] Yeah,
I'm a full-fledged samurai,

124
00:08:11,458 --> 00:08:12,791
but I can think like a bandit

125
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:16,833
when rude villagers need
to be taught a lesson. Eh?

126
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:26,833
Any objections, Grandpa?

127
00:08:26,916 --> 00:08:29,083
No...
Alright by me.

128
00:08:29,166 --> 00:08:31,250
[KIKUCHIYO] Ha, ha, ha, ha...

129
00:08:31,333 --> 00:08:33,916
If you think you can back out
now that you've brought us here,

130
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,291
you're wrong!

131
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:38,125
Bandits never forgive a
village that betrayed them.

132
00:08:38,208 --> 00:08:40,666
[VILLAGERS YELL FEARFULLY]

133
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:42,000
[KIKUCHIYO]
But don't worry!

134
00:08:42,083 --> 00:08:43,625
Now that I'm here,
everything's going to be fine.

135
00:08:43,708 --> 00:08:45,208
Let go of me,
you big pack-mule!

136
00:08:45,291 --> 00:08:47,583
[KIKUCHIYO] Okay, don't
get twitchy, sweetheart.

137
00:08:47,666 --> 00:08:50,958
Well I'll be damned,
the big oaf can be useful.

138
00:08:51,041 --> 00:08:52,083
[KAMBE] Heh, heh...

139
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:59,416
I've returned, Grandmother.

140
00:08:59,500 --> 00:09:01,208
Mm-Hmm...

141
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:03,166
And have you brought samurai?

142
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:05,208
Yes ma'am.
We brought seven of them!

143
00:09:05,291 --> 00:09:07,333
And are they
good samurai, child?

144
00:09:07,416 --> 00:09:09,833
Yes... I believe
they are, Grandmother.

145
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:12,708
Well... that's so
nice then, dear...

146
00:09:12,791 --> 00:09:16,166
Good samurai are very hard to
come by lately, you know...?

147
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,958
When I was young they weren't
so few and far between...

148
00:09:19,041 --> 00:09:22,041
but then those were
much better days.

149
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:48,375
[KIKUCHIYO] Oh, you
are so ravishing! Ha, ha!

150
00:09:48,458 --> 00:09:50,500
[KIKUCHIYO MAKES
MUSICAL NOISES]

151
00:09:50,583 --> 00:09:52,000
Oh, Rikichi!

152
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:55,791
I had no idea you had such
good taste in women's clothing.

153
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:02,291
Kikuchiyo.

154
00:10:03,500 --> 00:10:05,416
[KIKUCHIYO] Ha!
Who wants to dance with me?

155
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:08,833
Hey! Don't worry.
I wasn't going to pick you.

156
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:09,875
Kikuchiyo!

157
00:10:09,958 --> 00:10:11,708
Don't bother.
He wouldn't get it.

158
00:10:11,791 --> 00:10:13,750
[KIKUCHIYO] Get what?

159
00:10:27,250 --> 00:10:28,416
[MANZO YELLS]

160
00:10:31,250 --> 00:10:32,625
Oh, I was just, uh...

161
00:10:32,708 --> 00:10:35,208
...going to see how
the rice field was doing.

162
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:37,125
[MANZO SCREAMS]

163
00:10:42,791 --> 00:10:45,625
[KYUZO]
The war has already begun.

164
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:52,041
[SHICHIROJI]
I'm beginning to worry

165
00:10:52,125 --> 00:10:54,083
Rikichi's buying into
Manzo's paranoia...

166
00:10:54,166 --> 00:10:55,000
[HEIHACHI]
You might be right...

167
00:10:55,083 --> 00:10:55,875
[SHIKA]
Ooh, look at his sword!

168
00:10:55,958 --> 00:10:58,291
[UMA]
Does he kill people?

169
00:10:58,375 --> 00:10:59,583
He looked over here!

170
00:10:59,666 --> 00:11:01,750
He's as handsome as an actor.

171
00:11:01,833 --> 00:11:03,625
[HIE] And so much
more dangerous.

172
00:11:03,708 --> 00:11:04,708
[HIE GIGGLES]

173
00:11:07,958 --> 00:11:09,041
[GIRLS YELL]

174
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:10,666
[HIE] Oh my gosh,
he totally looked at me!

175
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:11,541
[UMA]
He was looking at me.

176
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:12,666
[SHIKA]
No. He looked at me!

177
00:11:12,750 --> 00:11:14,000
[UMA] Oh, you're delusional.

178
00:11:14,083 --> 00:11:15,083
[SHIKA] You always think
everyone's looking at you.

179
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:16,708
[HIE] He was practically
staring at me.

180
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:19,750
[OKARA] You're popular
with the girls, samurai.

181
00:11:19,833 --> 00:11:21,708
But your back is vulnerable...

182
00:11:21,791 --> 00:11:24,833
If I was an assassin,
you would already be dead.

183
00:11:24,916 --> 00:11:27,250
[OKARA AND KOMACHI LAUGH]

184
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:08,416
[OKARA YAWNS]

185
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:17,833
The preparations for
our defense begin now.

186
00:12:20,916 --> 00:12:23,416
We have been told the
Nobuseri have forty units...

187
00:12:23,500 --> 00:12:24,791
Has this changed?

188
00:12:24,875 --> 00:12:25,708
[ELDER GRUNTS]

189
00:12:25,791 --> 00:12:27,333
We've heard from
other villages--

190
00:12:27,416 --> 00:12:29,916
ten more big units, and
maybe sixty more footmen

191
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,833
and Yakan combat shells.

192
00:12:31,916 --> 00:12:36,041
We should send out a scout
soon for exact numbers.

193
00:12:36,125 --> 00:12:38,583
Heihachi-dono, you'll
be on weapons detail.

194
00:12:38,666 --> 00:12:40,666
[HEIHACHI GRUNTS]

195
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:43,708
Shichiroji, I trust you
know what to do... right?

196
00:12:43,791 --> 00:12:45,708
Just leave it to me.

197
00:12:45,791 --> 00:12:48,250
Kyuzo-dono, I want you
to gather the village men

198
00:12:48,333 --> 00:12:50,541
and teach them to
use a bow and arrow.

199
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:51,958
Understood.

200
00:12:53,875 --> 00:12:55,541
What should I do sensei?

201
00:12:55,625 --> 00:12:57,458
You'll be on guard duty.

202
00:12:57,541 --> 00:13:00,375
Oh, great. Guard duty.

203
00:13:00,458 --> 00:13:02,750
Do not let any enemy
scout get away...

204
00:13:02,833 --> 00:13:03,958
They cannot know about us

205
00:13:04,041 --> 00:13:06,666
before defensive
preparations are complete.

206
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:09,083
Yes sir!

207
00:13:09,166 --> 00:13:10,708
If we do not work together now,

208
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:13,208
then we've lost this war
before it's begun...

209
00:13:13,291 --> 00:13:15,750
Let us band together
against the Nobuseri

210
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,916
and defend Kanna Village!

211
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:25,166
[FARMERS MAKE
WEAK BATTLE CRIES]

212
00:13:27,083 --> 00:13:28,541
[KIRARA SIGHS]

213
00:13:28,625 --> 00:13:34,125
[ELDER MAKES STRONG
BATTLE CRIES]

214
00:13:34,208 --> 00:13:36,041
Ahhhh!

215
00:13:36,125 --> 00:13:41,083
Ahhhh! Ahhhh!
Ahhhh! Ahhhh! Ahhhh..!

216
00:13:47,333 --> 00:13:48,791
[KIKUCHIYO]  Heh...

217
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:02,000
I don't care what
the samurai say.

218
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:04,500
There's no way a few
rice farmers with arrows

219
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:06,000
can beat the Nobuseri.

220
00:14:06,083 --> 00:14:07,125
They're machines.

221
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:08,750
We don't even
stand a chance.

222
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,500
We should beg them for mercy.

223
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:12,125
Yes, I agree.

224
00:14:12,208 --> 00:14:15,416
A bandit patrol will be
here around 7 o'clock...

225
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:19,208
Maybe if we were to go and
appeal to them right away...

226
00:14:19,291 --> 00:14:20,500
You think they'd let us go?

227
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:21,125
[RUSTLING]

228
00:14:21,208 --> 00:14:22,166
[MEN YELL]

229
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:23,250
[KIKUCHIYO] Hey!

230
00:14:23,333 --> 00:14:26,000
That's what I call good timing!

231
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:27,500
Ahh...!

232
00:14:27,583 --> 00:14:29,291
[KIKUCHIYO]
Yeah, that should do for now...

233
00:14:29,375 --> 00:14:30,916
Alright. Let's begin.

234
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:31,791
[GONZO]
Begin what?

235
00:14:31,875 --> 00:14:33,625
[KIKUCHIYO]
Your training.

236
00:14:33,708 --> 00:14:34,791
All right, listen up!

237
00:14:34,875 --> 00:14:37,416
From this moment on,
I am your commander!

238
00:14:37,500 --> 00:14:38,875
[GONZO] Huh?

239
00:14:38,958 --> 00:14:41,250
[KIKUCHIYO]
Now stop whinin' and follow me!

240
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:49,333
Hello, water... miss me?

241
00:14:49,416 --> 00:14:50,666
[TORA] Kirara!

242
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,958
Kirara, there's something
we want to ask you.

243
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:55,416
[UMA]
It's about the samurai.

244
00:14:57,583 --> 00:15:00,083
Don't worry. They're all
very strong and reliable...

245
00:15:00,166 --> 00:15:01,833
Especially Kambe.
He's the most--

246
00:15:01,916 --> 00:15:03,333
We don't care about him!

247
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:05,333
[UMA] We want you to tell us
about the youngest samurai.

248
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:06,875
You know, the
handsome one!

249
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:09,083
You... You mean... Katsushiro?

250
00:15:09,166 --> 00:15:10,291
Oh! Katsushiro!

251
00:15:10,375 --> 00:15:14,791
Ohhhh! He's so cute!
What is he like?

252
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:18,083
He's a good person...
but I believe...

253
00:15:18,166 --> 00:15:20,833
...as a samurai he
still has a lot to learn.

254
00:15:20,916 --> 00:15:23,000
Yeah, we really
don't care about that!

255
00:15:23,083 --> 00:15:25,416
Does he have a wife or
girlfriend or anything?

256
00:15:25,500 --> 00:15:27,291
I don't know. I never asked.

257
00:15:27,375 --> 00:15:28,708
Come on, you have
to know something!

258
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:30,583
Now don't you
hold out on us.

259
00:15:30,666 --> 00:15:32,750
If you want to know so
badly ask him yourselves.

260
00:15:32,833 --> 00:15:35,125
No! We're too shy!

261
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:36,125
[KIRARA SIGHS]

262
00:15:51,208 --> 00:15:53,916
[GOROBE] Well... this
is an incredible place.

263
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,291
We believe it to be sacred.

264
00:15:58,125 --> 00:15:59,916
I think we can use these...

265
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:02,708
We're going to have
to chop a few down.

266
00:16:02,791 --> 00:16:06,083
I must warn you, however,
they won't come down so easily.

267
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:08,458
Heh... The tougher the better.

268
00:16:13,583 --> 00:16:15,958
Hold your breath
when you draw the bow.

269
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:17,291
Okay.

270
00:16:17,375 --> 00:16:19,416
See your enemy closer
to you than he really is.

271
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:21,833
Draw him to you, then fire.

272
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:25,791
[FARMERS YELL]

273
00:16:25,875 --> 00:16:27,125
[OKARA LAUGHS]

274
00:16:27,208 --> 00:16:28,416
[KOMACHI] Aww...

275
00:16:33,875 --> 00:16:35,083
[GOROBE]
There is one good thing.

276
00:16:35,166 --> 00:16:36,333
At least we won't
have to worry about

277
00:16:36,416 --> 00:16:38,083
them attacking us by water.

278
00:16:38,166 --> 00:16:41,916
Let's build a dam,
just to be safe.

279
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,541
Just beyond us is a waterfall.

280
00:16:49,291 --> 00:16:51,291
It's a bit deeper
than I thought...

281
00:16:51,375 --> 00:16:54,041
A difficult place to attack,
but also tough to defend.

282
00:16:54,125 --> 00:16:56,541
That will not escape
Shichiroji's notice.

283
00:16:56,625 --> 00:16:59,750
No. I guess not...
He is your right hand man.

284
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:07,750
I know it's heavy, guys, just
put it over there would you?

285
00:17:09,458 --> 00:17:10,500
What are you guys doing?

286
00:17:10,583 --> 00:17:12,416
We're strengthening
our defenses.

287
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,083
How ya gonna do that?

288
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:16,750
Kambe's planning to make this
little village into a fortress.

289
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,000
Kinda like a castle.

290
00:17:18,083 --> 00:17:19,916
This place is gonna be a castle?

291
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,083
An impenetrable one.

292
00:17:26,916 --> 00:17:29,750
The only problem is the sky.

293
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:31,041
Hey, sweetheart...?

294
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:32,541
I don't suppose you
know if the villagers

295
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:35,791
have any weapons
stashed away?

296
00:17:35,875 --> 00:17:38,250
They do, but
you can't have them.

297
00:17:46,208 --> 00:17:48,291
[KAMBE] We'll have to
destroy the bridge.

298
00:17:48,375 --> 00:17:49,833
[GOROBE] You may be right...

299
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:52,375
But what do we do about the
three homes on the other side?

300
00:17:52,458 --> 00:17:53,791
[KAMBE]
It's unavoidable.

301
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:55,625
To have any kind
of solid defense,

302
00:17:55,708 --> 00:17:59,291
they must, unfortunately,
be sacrificed.

303
00:18:05,375 --> 00:18:08,083
[KOMACHI] They've been here
since before we were born.

304
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:09,416
[OKARA]
They're broken.

305
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:11,041
These are a really
great find...

306
00:18:11,125 --> 00:18:12,333
Thanks, sweetheart.

307
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:14,375
[KOMACHI LAUGHS]

308
00:18:14,458 --> 00:18:15,833
[SHICHIROJI]
By the way...

309
00:18:15,916 --> 00:18:18,833
I've got a very important
mission for the two of you.

310
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:20,625
--[OKARA] Huh...
--[KOMACHI] Oh...!

311
00:18:22,083 --> 00:18:24,083
So, tell us about
yourself, samurai...

312
00:18:24,166 --> 00:18:25,916
Are you married?
Have a girlfriend?

313
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:29,125
Hey, less talkin',
more workin', grandma.

314
00:18:29,208 --> 00:18:31,083
[KOMACHI] Heihachi!

315
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:32,750
C'mon, c'mon.
Quick as you can...!

316
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:35,791
Momotaro has a question about
machines or something.

317
00:18:35,875 --> 00:18:37,916
[KIKUCHIYO]
Huh? Maybe I should handle this.

318
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,125
Nobody asked
for you, Kiku.

319
00:18:40,208 --> 00:18:42,000
[KIKUCHIYO GRUNTS]

320
00:18:43,791 --> 00:18:44,750
Dad, wait! Don't go!

321
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:46,333
Move, girl!

322
00:18:46,416 --> 00:18:49,083
You're going to sell the samurai
out to the bandits, aren't you?

323
00:18:49,166 --> 00:18:50,958
Did you know they're going
to destroy the bridge?

324
00:18:51,041 --> 00:18:53,416
That we'll be isolated from
the rest of the village...?

325
00:18:53,500 --> 00:18:55,166
If we're going to lose
our farm anyway,

326
00:18:55,250 --> 00:18:57,625
what was the point of hiring the
samurai in the first place?

327
00:18:57,708 --> 00:19:01,000
If it'll help save the village,
we have to make that sacrifice!

328
00:19:01,083 --> 00:19:02,958
I'm doing this
for you, girl...

329
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:05,708
Once our farm's been destroyed,
who will want to marry you?

330
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:08,083
What do I care?
I'll marry a samurai!

331
00:19:08,166 --> 00:19:09,250
[MANZO]
Foolish child!

332
00:19:09,333 --> 00:19:12,333
You will never disgrace
me in such a way!

333
00:19:12,416 --> 00:19:14,291
I hate you!

334
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:24,375
Oh yeah, I'm pretty sure
I can do what you want me to.

335
00:19:24,458 --> 00:19:26,416
[KIKUCHIYO] You guys
are having all the fun.

336
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,000
Hey! Kikuchiyo!

337
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:29,666
[KIKUCHIYO]
Can't hear you.

338
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,000
Kikuchiyo-dono...

339
00:19:31,083 --> 00:19:33,125
I think I'm gonna need
your help on this one.

340
00:19:33,208 --> 00:19:35,250
[KIKUCHIYO]
Oh! Why didn't you say so?

341
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:36,958
Be right down!

342
00:19:37,041 --> 00:19:38,125
[THUD]

343
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:50,208
Kirara! You have to
help me stop my dad

344
00:19:50,291 --> 00:19:53,083
before anyone finds out!

345
00:19:53,166 --> 00:19:54,958
He's going to
betray the village.

346
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:58,458
He's on his way to tell
the bandits about the samurai!

347
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:00,208
We can't allow
him to do that.

348
00:20:00,291 --> 00:20:03,250
But if that quiet samurai finds
out about Dad he'll kill him!

349
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:05,541
I know he will...! Kirara...

350
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:07,708
I'll think of something, Shino.

351
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:09,291
Oh, thank you.

352
00:20:09,375 --> 00:20:11,083
[KIRARA]
Now where is Manzo?

353
00:20:11,166 --> 00:20:12,416
[SHINO]
He's on the North cliff,

354
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:14,916
waiting for the
seven o'clock scout.

355
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,208
[KIRARA]
Katsushiro?

356
00:20:16,291 --> 00:20:20,041
You heard all of
that, didn't you?

357
00:20:20,125 --> 00:20:22,416
I would like to
ask for your help.

358
00:20:22,500 --> 00:20:24,541
I'll do my duty.

359
00:20:28,625 --> 00:20:31,500
All right big guy...
Nice and easy through here!

360
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:32,583
[KIKUCHIYO]
Uh, hey, so what are you

361
00:20:32,666 --> 00:20:34,000
gonna make with these things?

362
00:20:34,083 --> 00:20:36,208
Oh, you'll see.

363
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:49,125
There he is.

364
00:21:01,041 --> 00:21:02,583
[MANZO] Sir, you honor
me with your presence.

365
00:21:02,666 --> 00:21:04,666
[GENZO] Are there any
changes in the village?

366
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:05,625
[MANZO WHIMPERS]

367
00:21:05,708 --> 00:21:06,291
[GENZO] What is it?

368
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:07,791
[MANZO] I'm sorry!

369
00:21:07,875 --> 00:21:09,375
Tell me what happened.

370
00:21:09,458 --> 00:21:12,041
[MANZO]
S-Samurai came to the village.

371
00:21:12,125 --> 00:21:14,666
Samurai? How many of them?

372
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:16,250
[MANZO]
S-S-Seven, sir.

373
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:20,125
So it's those samurai...
They travel fast.

374
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:21,125
You've done well.

375
00:21:21,208 --> 00:21:22,208
[MANZO]
Thank you, sir.

376
00:21:22,291 --> 00:21:23,791
Great Samurai...

377
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:26,166
Don't worry, Shino.
I won't hurt your father.

378
00:21:26,250 --> 00:21:28,875
Can you defeat him?

379
00:21:28,958 --> 00:21:30,375
I must.

380
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,000
[KATSUSHIRO GASPS]

381
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:34,708
[KATSUSHIRO YELLS]

382
00:21:34,791 --> 00:21:35,625
[MANZO YELLS]

383
00:21:41,708 --> 00:21:43,791
I can't let you
leave here alive.

384
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:46,750
Heh... And how will 
you stop me, little boy?

385
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:48,041
You've betrayed me.

386
00:21:48,125 --> 00:21:49,208
No, Great One!

387
00:21:49,291 --> 00:21:50,875
That samurai just
followed me on his own,

388
00:21:50,958 --> 00:21:53,958
I swear to you! I didn't
know anything about it!

389
00:21:54,041 --> 00:21:55,916
[MANZO YELLS]

390
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,458
A pitiful excuse.

391
00:21:57,541 --> 00:21:58,291
Father!

392
00:21:58,375 --> 00:22:00,041
Katsushiro!

393
00:22:00,625 --> 00:22:02,500
[KATSUSHIRO YELLS]

394
00:22:12,541 --> 00:22:14,875
You're like a child
swinging a stick...

395
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:19,291
And children cannot kill...
They can only play pretend.

396
00:22:19,375 --> 00:22:21,916
Katsushiro, are you all right?

397
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:24,291
Find another job, kid.

398
00:22:25,666 --> 00:22:27,541
Get a hold of yourself!

399
00:22:31,916 --> 00:22:33,541
No you don't!

400
00:22:33,625 --> 00:22:36,708
[KATSUSHIRO YELLS]

401
00:22:42,583 --> 00:22:44,333
Impossible!

402
00:22:54,833 --> 00:22:56,541
[SHINO] Dad!

403
00:23:04,125 --> 00:23:06,416
Oh, Katsushiro.

404
00:23:13,333 --> 00:23:18,291
♪ closing song ♪

405
00:25:21,625 --> 00:25:23,375
[OKARA SNICKERS]

406
00:25:23,458 --> 00:25:25,083
[OKARA] Thanks for
your letters, Komachi.

407
00:25:25,166 --> 00:25:26,291
After all the time you spent

408
00:25:26,375 --> 00:25:28,000
bragging about
the "Great Samurai,"

409
00:25:28,083 --> 00:25:30,958
I couldn't wait to see
what the fuss was about.

410
00:25:31,041 --> 00:25:33,125
I asked other villagers
what they thought, too,

411
00:25:33,208 --> 00:25:35,875
but they were scared,
and wanted us to hide.

412
00:25:35,958 --> 00:25:38,208
At least, the men were scared.

413
00:25:38,291 --> 00:25:41,750
The girls were excited and
that made things even worse.

414
00:25:41,833 --> 00:25:44,375
You know Shino--
she's really pretty, right?

415
00:25:44,458 --> 00:25:47,166
Well her ugly old dad chopped
all her hair off like a boy's,

416
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:49,708
'cause he's afraid of these
warriors running off with her.

417
00:25:49,791 --> 00:25:53,708
So yeah, all this samurai talk's
made everyone a little crazy.

418
00:25:53,791 --> 00:25:56,250
But now that they're here--
what a let down.

419
00:25:56,333 --> 00:25:59,500
They're all old, and their faces
are rough and full of scars.

420
00:25:59,583 --> 00:26:01,666
And I haven't seen them swing
their swords or anything.

421
00:26:01,750 --> 00:26:04,916
They just sit around
and talk plans. Boring!

422
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:06,875
The only cute one is
that young Katsushiro.

423
00:26:06,958 --> 00:26:09,166
So the older girls
are fighting over him.

424
00:26:09,250 --> 00:26:12,541
I doubt they stand a chance,
but it's fun to watch 'em try...

425
00:26:12,625 --> 00:26:14,708
Anyway, these samurai
are eating our rice,

426
00:26:14,791 --> 00:26:16,500
so they better be
as good as you wrote.

427
00:26:16,583 --> 00:26:18,458
But I guess
we'll find out soon...

428
00:26:18,541 --> 00:26:20,000
[OKARA SNICKERS]

